All,

I think we're ready to cut a 4.10 beta 1 release from head, including
a raft of bug fixes, most notably the fix in the contents of junit-dep
as released to maven.  Of those of you who plan on being beta-testers:

1) Is there anyone who plans to download the jar directly from github
for testing?
2) Is there anyone who plans to set the junit version in their pom to
LATEST, and add https://oss.sonatype.org/content/groups/public as a
repository, in order to test through maven?

I'm happy to support both beta-release paths if it turns out people
are using both.

   David Saff
